3. cs.CL - The paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as text classification and language modelling, which are part of Computational Linguistics.
4. cs.CY - The paper deals with the development of an Intelligent Tutoring System, which involves the use of computer systems to facilitate learning, falling under the domain of Cybernetics.
5. cs.ED - The paper deals with the development of a model for knowledge tracing in the context of education, which falls under the domain of Computer Science Education.
